        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Correlator Setup for 0.2'' ALMA observations at 265.9 GHz

In this band we target the J=3-2 transition of HCN (265.87 GHz) in baseband 1, a
continuum measurement in baseband 2, and a group of NO J=5/2-3/2 transitions 
(around 250.63 GHz) in baseband 3. The linewidths in this face-on source are of 
order 1 km/s, setting the desired spectral resolution of HCN to 0.069 km/s for 
HCN and 0.292 km/s for NO. Spectral resolution for NO is also determined by the 
desire to include all of the NO J=5/2-3/2 transitions in one spectral window.

Requested Sensitivity for 0.2'' ALMA observations at 265.9 GHz

In TW Hya the column density goes as roughly 1/r (Andrews et al. 2012) and the 
emitting area as r^2.  Thus, roughly the flux will scale with radius.
Emission lines from two molecular species and one continuum setting are 
requested within this science goal. The primary requested molecular transition, 
HCN 3-2, has been previously detected in this source (Qi et al. 2008) with the 
Submillimeter Array. In the SMA observations using a 1.3?? beam and spectral 
resolution 0.23 km/s, HCN 3-2 had a peak flux of 4.7 Jy.
We will observe with high dv = 0.069 km/s, but our sensitivitiy calculations 
will smooth to 0.275 km/s.
Thus the observed flux should be 4.7 * (0.2 /1.3) * (0.275 / 0.23) = 0.864 Jy 
using our settings.
To achieve a 10 sigma detection of HCN 3-2, the rms sensitivity should be 86 
mJy when smoothed to 0.275 km/s; because this is a particularly bright 
transition, we choose 11 mJy at 0.07 km/s with essentially no increase in 
observing time to help boost the NO measurement.

The continuum flux of 250 mJy is estimated from the ~0.6" angular resolution
observations of TW Hya at 870 microns by Andrews et al. 2012, ApJ, 744, 162.   
Assuming the flux scales as nu^3 this gives 125 mJy at 1.11 mm.
The surface density generally scales as 1/r with
surface area going as r^2.  Thus we assume the continuum scales with
radius giving ~41 mJy
Thus the expected line rms to continuum is 11.0mJy/41 mJy or 1:4.

Imaging requirements:
We request observations with two 12m array configurations to achieve sensitivity
to scales of 0.2'' (11 AU) and to the outer disk (~100 AU). The high resolution 
configuration is motivated by a goal of resolving the radial abundance and 
excitation temperature structure of HCN, while the compact configuration is to 
detect emission from the outer disk, which is important for making overall 
abundance measurements.</prj:justificationText>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
